airplane hangar

981
00:45:59,250 --> 00:46:00,541
with the exception
of the angled

982
00:46:00,708 --> 00:46:02,166
doors that
I mentioned before.

983
00:46:02,333 --> 00:46:03,791
This hangar was equipped
with typical tools

984
00:46:03,958 --> 00:46:05,750
and extensive electronic
equipment.

985
00:46:06,250 --> 00:46:08,333
It also had a machine with
an X-ray emblem on it

986
00:46:08,500 --> 00:46:11,041
and an overhead crane
rated at 20,000 pounds.

987
00:46:11,416 --> 00:46:14,166
Equipment in this hangar was
marked with a black number 41

988
00:46:14,333 --> 00:46:15,833
with a white circle around it.

989
00:46:16,250 --> 00:46:19,791
Well, the hangar was lit by
mercury vapor lights.

990
00:46:20,166 --> 00:46:21,750
I don't--
cone-shaped lights.

991
00:46:21,916 --> 00:46:24,125
There was a countless number
of them on the ceiling.

992
00:46:24,291 --> 00:46:28,375
Um, in addition to those, there
were, uh, tripod halogen lights,

993
00:46:28,541 --> 00:46:30,250
dual head halogen lights set up.

994
00:46:30,458 --> 00:46:32,625
And those really provided
a lot of bright light

995
00:46:32,791 --> 00:46:34,250
for working close up and,

996
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:36,250
uh... [stutters]
those were a lot more

997
00:46:36,416 --> 00:46:37,875
useful than the overhead lights.

998
00:46:40,166 --> 00:46:41,625
I had at least partial views

999
00:46:41,791 --> 00:46:44,083
of the nine different discs
out at S4.

1000
00:46:44,250 --> 00:46:46,666
But the one I'm going to
describe to you now

1001
00:46:46,875 --> 00:46:48,583
is the one in which
I not only saw

1002
00:46:48,750 --> 00:46:50,541
two of the three
interior levels,

1003
00:46:51,083 --> 00:46:53,375
but I also saw it fully
functional in flight.

1004
00:46:53,916 --> 00:46:57,125
This particular disc appeared
to be in excellent condition.

1005
00:46:57,375 --> 00:46:58,791
And because of its
sleek appearance,

1006
00:46:58,958 --> 00:47:00,625
I nicknamed it
"The sport model."

1007
00:47:01,666 --> 00:47:04,083
Now, previously I had estimated
the sport model to be

1008
00:47:04,250 --> 00:47:06,750
about 15 feet high and
about 40 feet wide.

1009
00:47:06,958 --> 00:47:09,583
But since then I've
enlisted some expert help

1010
00:47:09,750 --> 00:47:11,375
from the field of
computer imaging.

1011
00:47:11,625 --> 00:47:13,500
And together we've
scaled the disc up

1012
00:47:13,666 --> 00:47:16,333
from the size of components
which I had a close look at

1013
00:47:16,500 --> 00:47:19,250
and could accurately
establish their actual size.

1014
00:47:19,541 --> 00:47:22,166
From this analysis
I'm now presenting to you

1015
00:47:22,333 --> 00:47:24,375
the most accurate
information I can convey

1016
00:47:24,541 --> 00:47:26,625
regarding the disc's
physical structure.

1017
00:47:26,833 --> 00:47:28,750
The sport model is 16 feet tall

1018
00:47:28,916 --> 00:47:31,416
and 52 feet 9 inches
in diameter.

1019
00:47:32,375 --> 00:47:34,125
The exterior skin of
the disc is metal,

1020
00:47:34,291 --> 00:47:36,625
which is the color of
unpolished stainless steel.

1021
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:39,875
The sport model sits on its
belly when it's not energized

1022
00:47:40,041 --> 00:47:42,458
and not the stereotypical
tripod legs

1023
00:47:42,750 --> 00:47:45,791
that folklore usually
associates with
this type of craft.

1024
00:47:46,666 --> 00:47:48,166
As you can see the entry hatch

1025
00:47:48,333 --> 00:47:50,500
is located on the upper
half of the disc

1026
00:47:50,750 --> 00:47:52,750
with just the bottom
portion of the door

1027
00:47:52,916 --> 00:47:54,875
wrapping around the
center lip of the disc.

1028
00:47:55,333 --> 00:47:58,166
The interior of the disc is
divided into three levels.

1029
00:47:58,750 --> 00:48:01,250
The lower level is where
the three gravity emitters

1030
00:48:01,416 --> 00:48:03,250
and their wave guides
are located.

1031
00:48:04,625 --> 00:48:05,958
These are the
integral components

1032
00:48:06,125 --> 00:48:07,708
of the propulsion system

1033
00:48:07,875 --> 00:48:10,541
that are used to amplify
and focus the gravity "A" wave.

1034
00:48:10,875 --> 00:48:14,291
The reactor is located
directly above the three
gravity emitters

1035
00:48:14,458 --> 00:48:17,500
on the center level, and is in
fact, centered between them.

1036
00:48:18,083 --> 00:48:20,458
The center level of the disc
houses the amplifier heads

1037
00:48:20,625 --> 00:48:22,708
as well as the seats which
were too small and

1038
00:48:22,875 --> 00:48:24,458
too low to the floor
to be functional

1039
00:48:24,625 --> 00:48:25,875
for adult human beings.

1040
00:48:26,166 --> 00:48:27,750
The walls of the
center level are all

1041
00:48:27,916 --> 00:48:29,583
divided into archways.

1042
00:48:29,750 --> 00:48:32,041
At one point in time when
the disc was energized

1043
00:48:32,333 --> 00:48:34,375
one of the archways
became transparent

1044
00:48:34,541 --> 00:48:36,666
and you could see
the area outside of it,

1045
00:48:36,916 --> 00:48:39,000
just as if the archway
was a window.

1046
00:48:39,541 --> 00:48:41,041
Then a form of writing,

1047
00:48:41,208 --> 00:48:43,125
which was unlike any
alphabetic, scientific,

1048
00:48:43,291 --> 00:48:45,250
or mathematical symbols
I've ever seen,

1049
00:48:45,416 --> 00:48:48,458
began to appear on one side
of the transparent archway.

1050
00:48:48,750 --> 00:48:51,291
I was never given access to
the upper level of the disc

1051
00:48:51,458 --> 00:48:54,708
so I can't enlighten you as to
what the porthole-like
areas are

1052
00:48:54,916 --> 00:48:57,291
other than that, I can assure
you, they're not portholes.

1053
00:49:00,583 --> 00:49:03,125
Any time... I was in
the big hangar

1054
00:49:03,291 --> 00:49:06,750
my eyes were always focused
right on the sport model.

1055
00:49:07,250 --> 00:49:10,208
There could have been fires
going on on either side of me

1056
00:49:10,375 --> 00:49:13,041
and I would still have been
looking at it.

1057
00:49:13,458 --> 00:49:15,500
It-- It was that captivating.

1058
00:49:16,083 --> 00:49:17,875
When I was close to
the sport model,

1059
00:49:18,250 --> 00:49:21,000
I really focused on
the skin of the craft.

1060
00:49:21,416 --> 00:49:24,000
What it looked like,
how it changed, the color.

1061
00:49:24,833 --> 00:49:28,041
It has a small antenna looking
device which is actually

1062
00:49:28,208 --> 00:49:30,500
a waveguide, that protrudes
from the top.

1063
00:49:30,833 --> 00:49:33,458
It is like a pewter gray
in color.

1064
00:49:33,750 --> 00:49:35,208
It appears to be metal.

1065
00:49:35,375 --> 00:49:37,083
I felt it. It's cold.

1066
00:49:37,333 --> 00:49:40,500
It may not be. It might be some
advanced ceramic of some type.

1067
00:49:42,041 --> 00:49:44,333
So the body of the craft
had ripples.

1068
00:49:44,500 --> 00:49:47,500
The-- one of them we call
the insulation ring.

1069
00:49:47,708 --> 00:49:49,583
It was a dark black color.

1070
00:49:49,958 --> 00:49:51,583
The only thing on the outside

1071
00:49:51,750 --> 00:49:53,708
that was a different color
than the craft.

1072
00:49:53,958 --> 00:49:55,541
We call it the insulation
ring because

1073
00:49:55,708 --> 00:49:57,708
when the craft is in operation

1074
00:49:58,166 --> 00:50:00,750
there is a high voltage
detectable on--

1075
00:50:01,291 --> 00:50:02,666
on the skin of the craft,

1076
00:50:02,958 --> 00:50:05,833
but that high voltage is not
present above that ring.

1077
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:09,375
The upper part of the craft
above the insulation ring

1078
00:50:09,583 --> 00:50:11,500
were what we call
the planar arrays.

1079
00:50:11,666 --> 00:50:15,791
Flat window-looking,
porthole-looking openings
in the craft.

1080
00:50:15,958 --> 00:50:18,375
They-- they were unusually dark.

1081
00:50:18,583 --> 00:50:22,333
Really dark. Almost looked like
holes, although there weren't.

1082
00:50:23,208 --> 00:50:27,083
It was theorized that they were
used to determine the craft's

1083
00:50:27,250 --> 00:50:28,750
location in space.

1084
00:50:28,958 --> 00:50:31,666
Each one of them,
looking out in space

1085
00:50:31,833 --> 00:50:35,250
apparently looking at star
positions or whatever e--

1086
00:50:35,541 --> 00:50:38,750
energy or light it uses to
locate its place.

1087
00:50:38,916 --> 00:50:42,375
Each one looking in a
different direction and then

1088
00:50:42,625 --> 00:50:44,750
some sort of computer, uh,

1089
00:50:44,916 --> 00:50:47,416
in the upper level that
takes that data

1090
00:50:47,875 --> 00:50:50,291
and figures out its location.

1091
00:50:51,500 --> 00:50:54,083
Again, I may be
completely wrong,

1092
00:50:54,458 --> 00:50:56,500
or the people that came up with
that may be completely wrong

1093
00:50:56,666 --> 00:50:59,125
but I would agree with that
just looking at it, that--

1094
00:50:59,750 --> 00:51:02,500
that it has to be something
along those lines.

1095
00:51:02,958 --> 00:51:04,166
I walked up to the stairs

1096
00:51:04,333 --> 00:51:06,041
that led to the entrance
of the craft.

1097
00:51:06,875 --> 00:51:10,208
I remember, climbing the stairs,
how excited I was,

1098
00:51:10,750 --> 00:51:13,625
to finally get to see
what's inside the craft.

1099
00:51:15,041 --> 00:51:17,875
When I got to the top of the
stairs I can clearly see

1100
00:51:18,041 --> 00:51:20,166
the reversed American flag
to my left.

1101
00:51:20,958 --> 00:51:23,333
The hatchway is
fairly small and I put

1102
00:51:23,666 --> 00:51:27,250
my hands on both sides of
it to bend down to go inside

1103
00:51:27,583 --> 00:51:30,291
and when I did, my hand was near

1104
00:51:30,791 --> 00:51:33,666
the reversed American flag so
I noticed the exact size,

1105
00:51:33,833 --> 00:51:36,958
it was just a little more than
a span, a little more than

1106
00:51:37,375 --> 00:51:39,291
you know, as far as
my fingers stretched

1107
00:51:39,458 --> 00:51:42,875
and I glanced down and
looked at the security guard

1108
00:51:43,041 --> 00:51:45,958
who was staring at me and
just kind of gave him a smile,

1109
00:51:46,416 --> 00:51:48,875
and, you know,
proceeded into the craft.

1110
00:51:49,250 --> 00:51:51,291
[ominous, sci-fi music]

1111
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:02,875
I was shocked at how sparse the
inside of the craft was.

1112
00:52:03,291 --> 00:52:06,291
Everything was the same color,
the same texture,

1113
00:52:06,750 --> 00:52:09,083
and it all appeared to be
the same material.

1114
00:52:09,416 --> 00:52:12,708
Virtually everything had a
radius of curvature to it

1115
00:52:12,916 --> 00:52:15,125
and everything looked like
it was molded together,

1116
00:52:15,375 --> 00:52:17,208
with the exception
of the reactor.

1117
00:52:17,416 --> 00:52:19,583
Even though there were
two tripod lights set up

1118
00:52:19,750 --> 00:52:22,500
inside the craft,
it was still very dark.

1119
00:52:23,291 --> 00:52:25,375
I've often described the
interior of the craft

1120
00:52:25,541 --> 00:52:27,166
as being very ominous.

1121
00:52:28,875 --> 00:52:30,625
I got to look inside and it had

1122
00:52:31,166 --> 00:52:33,958
really small chairs and
I think that was the first...

1123
00:52:34,833 --> 00:52:37,458
...confirmation I had,
that was just a shocking thing

1124
00:52:37,625 --> 00:52:40,125
because it-- every time before
that I was able to label it

1125
00:52:40,291 --> 00:52:41,416
"Well this is just...

1126
00:52:42,875 --> 00:52:44,458
...oh, a little advance that
a group of

1127
00:52:44,625 --> 00:52:46,166
scientists had
formed and, you know, they're

1128
00:52:46,333 --> 00:52:47,916
keeping it secret"
and, "Yeah, we could have built

1129
00:52:48,083 --> 00:52:49,958
a big disc like that,
that's no problem and

1130
00:52:50,125 --> 00:52:52,583
you know, we could have adapted
these to make it fly," but...

1131
00:52:53,625 --> 00:52:55,166
...why does it have little
furniture inside?

1132
00:52:55,333 --> 00:52:57,041
Essentially a little seat
and now and it--

1133
00:52:57,458 --> 00:53:00,083
And things began to click
together just all too fast.

1134
00:53:01,583 --> 00:53:03,916
I was in there with
my lab partner Barry

1135
00:53:04,458 --> 00:53:08,041
and there was also another team
working elsewhere in the craft.

1136
00:53:08,833 --> 00:53:11,458
While going over
the reactor placement

1137
00:53:11,625 --> 00:53:14,375
Barry drew my attention
to the archways

1138
00:53:14,583 --> 00:53:16,625
that all surrounded
the interior of the craft

1139
00:53:16,791 --> 00:53:19,916
explaining they were hollow,
and actually waveguides.

1140
00:53:20,250 --> 00:53:21,791
The waveguide, which...

1141
00:53:22,125 --> 00:53:25,208
terminates, is the antenna
looking object from the top.

1142
00:53:25,666 --> 00:53:29,333
Yeah, that kind of folds
down on itself so it

1143
00:53:29,833 --> 00:53:33,125
extends and retracts and that
sits on the top of the reactor

1144
00:53:33,291 --> 00:53:37,708
that essentially channels
the gravity wave up there

1145
00:53:37,916 --> 00:53:40,500
and into the superstructure
around the craft

1146
00:53:40,666 --> 00:53:42,416
so it's dispersed evenly.

1147
00:53:42,833 --> 00:53:45,416
While we were working
next to the reactor

1148
00:53:45,625 --> 00:53:48,333
I got a really good look
at the three seats

1149
00:53:48,500 --> 00:53:50,375
or what we assumed to be seats,

1150
00:53:50,541 --> 00:53:54,708
that were far too small to be
usable by an adult human.

1151
00:53:56,291 --> 00:53:58,291
You know, if you look
at the seats

1152
00:53:58,458 --> 00:54:00,583
what I call the seats,
the placement,

1153
00:54:00,750 --> 00:54:03,041
one of them,
the waveguide in the reactor

1154
00:54:03,208 --> 00:54:05,666
is directly in front of a seat.

1155
00:54:07,541 --> 00:54:09,583
-[mumbles]
-Why would you ever do that?

1156
00:54:09,750 --> 00:54:13,000
I mean, either... [chuckles]
the guy that sits in that seat

1157
00:54:13,166 --> 00:54:15,750
-is on reactor watch and
he just sits there and
-[chuckles]

1158
00:54:15,916 --> 00:54:17,791
makes sure everything
runs the all but...

1159
00:54:18,125 --> 00:54:20,750
it doesn't make any--
and that's the only one

1160
00:54:20,916 --> 00:54:25,000
that faces directly at the
panel that became transparent.

1161
00:54:25,458 --> 00:54:27,500
While we were working
on the reactor

1162
00:54:27,666 --> 00:54:31,208
I saw one of the archways
become completely transparent,

1163
00:54:31,375 --> 00:54:33,291
where I could see
outside the craft.

1164
00:54:33,458 --> 00:54:35,541
This immediately
caught my attention

1165
00:54:35,708 --> 00:54:37,083
and as I focused on it

1166
00:54:37,250 --> 00:54:40,083
half that archway turned
an opaque blue,

1167
00:54:40,250 --> 00:54:42,750
and black symbols
began to appear

1168
00:54:43,041 --> 00:54:45,416
on that blue portion
of the archway.

1169
00:54:45,875 --> 00:54:48,541
I'd never really seen
symbols like that before,

1170
00:54:48,708 --> 00:54:51,000
but my closest analogy to it

1171
00:54:51,375 --> 00:54:53,250
would be... Korean writing.

1172
00:54:53,708 --> 00:54:56,041
The symbols themselves
were not completely static.

1173
00:54:56,208 --> 00:54:58,583
They were slowly tilting
back and forth.

1174
00:54:59,083 --> 00:55:02,416
While that archway had my
attention, my lab partner Barry

1175
00:55:02,708 --> 00:55:04,166
whispered my name to me

1176
00:55:04,333 --> 00:55:06,500
to get my attention back to
where it belonged.

1177
00:55:07,708 --> 00:55:10,916
When I was in the craft... and

1178
00:55:11,250 --> 00:55:14,875
I was kneeling down by
the reactor and looked up at

1179
00:55:15,125 --> 00:55:17,458
the screen, Barry just said,

1180
00:55:17,666 --> 00:55:18,791
"Bob, Bob,"

1181
00:55:19,500 --> 00:55:21,458
you know, like,
"What are you doing?"

1182
00:55:21,750 --> 00:55:24,000
"That's not you," you know,
"look down here,"

1183
00:55:24,166 --> 00:55:26,750
which is what broke
my attention, to go there.

1184
00:55:27,083 --> 00:55:29,625
But yeah, and-- but when he--
my point was when he said it,

1185
00:55:29,791 --> 00:55:31,166
he-- he just kind of
whispered it.

1186
00:55:31,333 --> 00:55:33,291
It's like-- it's like you're
in a library,

1187
00:55:33,458 --> 00:55:35,041
-you know, so there's no--
-[interviewer] Mm.

1188
00:55:35,208 --> 00:55:36,916
no loud talking.
"Hey Bill,

1189
00:55:37,083 --> 00:55:38,333
get me--"
you know, it's just like...

1190
00:55:38,500 --> 00:55:40,416
[whispering mumbles]

1191
00:55:40,625 --> 00:55:43,916
So, I don't know the reasoning
behind that, but you know,

1192
00:55:44,083 --> 00:55:45,666
it's-- it's like a library.

1193
00:55:46,583 --> 00:55:49,000
I can see that the craft had
been worked on before

1194
00:55:49,166 --> 00:55:51,041
and probably for
quite some time.

1195
00:55:51,208 --> 00:55:54,916
One of the amplifiers had been
cut out with a plasma cutter.

1196
00:55:55,291 --> 00:55:59,000
Other teams were working
on the skin of the craft,

1197
00:55:59,666 --> 00:56:02,875
and there were lights, extension
cords, and other equipment

1198
00:56:03,416 --> 00:56:06,041
that were all over
the inside of the craft.

1199
00:56:06,500 --> 00:56:09,708
[interviewer] You had noticed
that one of the amplifiers

1200
00:56:09,875 --> 00:56:12,083
had been cut out of the craft.

1201
00:56:12,625 --> 00:56:13,666
Yeah.

1202
00:56:14,083 --> 00:56:15,291
[interviewer]
You know, you said

1203
00:56:15,458 --> 00:56:17,291
"They must have
really been sure."

1204
00:56:17,541 --> 00:56:21,000
You had to been a hundred
percent confident,

1205
00:56:21,791 --> 00:56:25,958
that... you weren't gonna
ruin the operation of anything

1206
00:56:26,125 --> 00:56:29,166
if you went to the
lenghts to remove

1207
00:56:29,791 --> 00:56:32,041
an entire amplifier
out of the craft.

1208
00:56:32,208 --> 00:56:33,666
Now... look,

1209
00:56:33,833 --> 00:56:35,375
once you remove that out,

1210
00:56:35,541 --> 00:56:38,916
the craft can't operate in--
in Delta mode anymore,

1211
00:56:39,208 --> 00:56:41,625
which makes you wonder
if they did that...

1212
00:56:42,250 --> 00:56:45,375
intentionally, so it couldn't
operate in that mode, you know,

1213
00:56:45,541 --> 00:56:48,000
kind of the equivalent of
clipping a bird's wings,

1214
00:56:48,166 --> 00:56:49,708
keeping it, you know, so it

1215
00:56:49,875 --> 00:56:51,166
can't fly away anywhere.

1216
00:56:51,791 --> 00:56:55,750
Somewhere, someone, and probably
certainly more than one person,

1217
00:56:56,250 --> 00:56:58,208
uh, a group of people
agreed that,

1218
00:56:58,375 --> 00:56:59,541
"Let's go take that out,"

1219
00:56:59,708 --> 00:57:01,833
and they had a damn good
reason to do it.

1220
00:57:05,458 --> 00:57:07,208
But they must have been
absolutely convinced,

1221
00:57:07,375 --> 00:57:09,250
they knew what was going on.
Removed it.

1222
00:57:09,958 --> 00:57:11,416
Moved it into the lab,

1223
00:57:11,833 --> 00:57:14,500
and they were still able to
operate the craft without it.

1224
00:57:14,666 --> 00:57:18,291
So, that uh-- clearly a lot
went on before I got there.

1225
00:57:20,958 --> 00:57:24,458
At one point, Barry instructed
me to go behind the seats

1226
00:57:24,875 --> 00:57:27,333
and pointed towards a small

1227
00:57:27,500 --> 00:57:30,166
honeycombed hatchway,
flush with the floor.

1228
00:57:30,875 --> 00:57:33,125
We both crawled over
to the hatchway,

1229
00:57:33,291 --> 00:57:36,750
and Barry showed me where to put
my finger in and pull backwards,

1230
00:57:37,166 --> 00:57:39,958
and... the little honeycombed
hatchway collapsed,

1231
00:57:40,291 --> 00:57:42,083
leaving an opening in the floor,

1232
00:57:42,250 --> 00:57:44,166
big enough to
barely squeeze through,

1233
00:57:44,333 --> 00:57:46,583
and look down into
the lower level.

1234
00:57:47,125 --> 00:57:51,250
I was able to get the upper part
of my body into the hatchway,

1235
00:57:51,416 --> 00:57:55,000
and got a good view of the
three emitters, hanging below.

1236
00:57:55,333 --> 00:57:57,041
The lower level was very dark.

1237
00:57:57,291 --> 00:57:59,291
There was just enough
light coming in,

1238
00:57:59,458 --> 00:58:02,791
under the entrance hatchway,
to see the emitters

1239
00:58:02,958 --> 00:58:04,541
and the lower part of the craft.

1240
00:58:04,875 --> 00:58:06,666
The emitters were the only
things that were

1241
00:58:06,833 --> 00:58:07,833
a-- a different color.

1242
00:58:08,000 --> 00:58:09,166
They were black.

1243
00:58:09,375 --> 00:58:11,666
The bottoms of them...
were hollow

1244
00:58:11,958 --> 00:58:13,541
and you could see

1245
00:58:13,708 --> 00:58:17,416
some sort of copper
colored plates inside there.

1246
00:58:17,750 --> 00:58:22,041
They were hung by
large diameter tubes,

1247
00:58:22,208 --> 00:58:23,958
maybe three inches or so,

1248
00:58:24,291 --> 00:58:25,708
just like the waveguide

1249
00:58:25,875 --> 00:58:28,083
that extends down
onto the reactor.

1250
00:58:30,958 --> 00:58:33,250
When all three of the
amplifiers are being
used for travel,

1251
00:58:33,416 --> 00:58:35,041
they're in the Delta
configuration.

1252
00:58:35,375 --> 00:58:37,208
And when only one is
being used for travel,

1253
00:58:37,375 --> 00:58:38,708
it's in the Omicron
configuration.

1254
00:58:38,875 --> 00:58:40,333
So as far as propulsion,

1255
00:58:40,500 --> 00:58:42,750
the craft operates in
two different modes,

1256
00:58:43,083 --> 00:58:45,500
called Omicron and Delta.

1257
00:58:45,791 --> 00:58:48,541
Omicron meaning one and
Delta meaning three,

1258
00:58:48,708 --> 00:58:51,333
and that's referring to
how many of the amplifiers and

1259
00:58:51,500 --> 00:58:53,000
emitters are being used.

1260
00:58:53,291 --> 00:58:57,125
So in Omicron configuration, the
craft lifts off the ground

1261
00:58:57,458 --> 00:58:59,625
using one amplifier
and one emitter.

1262
00:59:00,041 --> 00:59:03,166
The other two emitters
can swing all the way up to

1263
00:59:03,333 --> 00:59:05,875
180 degrees out the side
of the craft,

1264
00:59:06,208 --> 00:59:08,750
and what that does
is cause distortion

1265
00:59:09,333 --> 00:59:12,458
in space and kind of
forces the craft

1266
00:59:12,791 --> 00:59:15,000
to fall into that distortion.

1267
00:59:15,375 --> 00:59:18,166
Kind of the opposite of the way
our aircraft work.

1268
00:59:18,333 --> 00:59:21,208
Instead of throwing material
out the back,

1269
00:59:21,375 --> 00:59:23,625
this causes some
sort of distortion

1270
00:59:23,958 --> 00:59:26,333
in front of it,
where it's drawn into.

1271
00:59:26,833 --> 00:59:28,541
[soft eerie music]

1272
00:59:29,625 --> 00:59:33,791
The other mode of operation,
Delta configuration,

1273
00:59:34,291 --> 00:59:38,166
is really used when the craft
is outside the atmosphere

1274
00:59:38,333 --> 00:59:39,916
where it's sitting in
free space.

1275
00:59:40,291 --> 00:59:42,791
In that mode, the craft rotates
on its side.

1276
00:59:42,958 --> 00:59:46,500
It does a belly roll, and faces
the bottom of the craft

1277
00:59:46,666 --> 00:59:48,250
towards the destination.

1278
00:59:48,625 --> 00:59:52,000
The three emitters,
in the bottom of the craft,

1279
00:59:52,166 --> 00:59:53,791
focus on the destination.

1280
00:59:54,125 --> 00:59:56,875
They're brought up to power
and the craft makes a jump.

1281
00:59:57,458 --> 01:00:01,958
Now, the amplifiers don't
operate on a continuous fashion.

1282
01:00:02,208 --> 01:00:03,416
They pulse.

1283
01:00:03,583 --> 01:00:05,458
They produce a pulse of energy

1284
01:00:05,625 --> 01:00:08,875
and then require a recycle time.

1285
01:00:09,125 --> 01:00:10,958
It's somewhere around
10 milliseconds

1286
01:00:11,125 --> 01:00:12,708
or something like that,

1287
01:00:13,416 --> 01:00:16,541
but... then they essentially
can fire again

1288
01:00:16,791 --> 01:00:17,750
and make another jump.

1289
01:00:17,916 --> 01:00:19,125
So, in traveling to

1290
01:00:19,291 --> 01:00:20,583
a distant location,

1291
01:00:20,750 --> 01:00:22,875
the craft will make
several jumps.

1292
01:00:23,166 --> 01:00:25,750
It's never just one long jump,
you know,

1293
01:00:25,916 --> 01:00:27,833
across the galaxy or
something like that.

1294
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:30,041
It's just a series of jumps
and that's--

1295
01:00:30,208 --> 01:00:31,375
that's how it moves.

1296
01:00:31,625 --> 01:00:33,291
When it arrives to where it is,

1297
01:00:33,541 --> 01:00:35,583
it'll get close to
the destination,

1298
01:00:35,916 --> 01:00:37,666
switch over to Omicron mode,

1299
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:41,583
and... set down or cruise
around or whatever its plan was.

1300
01:00:42,333 --> 01:00:44,375
[suspenseful music]

1301
01:00:47,541 --> 01:00:50,416
As I went through the other
folders, there was, uh,

1302
01:00:50,666 --> 01:00:53,166
another project called Sidekick,
which dealt

1303
01:00:53,333 --> 01:00:57,041
with any weapon potential
of this spacecraft.

1304
01:00:57,208 --> 01:00:58,500
That was w--
weapons applications,

1305
01:00:58,666 --> 01:01:00,541
and I knew a little bit
more about that.

1306
01:01:00,708 --> 01:01:04,083
That was because the-- the
gravity amplifiers were used

1307
01:01:04,708 --> 01:01:09,166
as a-- a collimating device to--
I mean, to-- to narrow the beam

1308
01:01:09,500 --> 01:01:12,416
of something that appeared to be
like a particle weapon.

1309
01:01:12,583 --> 01:01:15,416
And it seemed to be dealing
with an accelerated particle

1310
01:01:15,583 --> 01:01:18,958
of some kind that was focused
or held in place,

1311
01:01:19,458 --> 01:01:23,250
and prevented from dispersing by
the gravity amplifiers,

1312
01:01:23,416 --> 01:01:25,666
by the emitters, actually.

1313
01:01:29,416 --> 01:01:32,958
Project Looking Glass
had to do with using the...

1314
01:01:33,541 --> 01:01:35,916
gravity amplifiers
to distort time.

1315
01:01:36,666 --> 01:01:38,958
And, you know, th--
this isn't implying that

1316
01:01:39,125 --> 01:01:40,958
they were trying
to make a time machine,

1317
01:01:41,166 --> 01:01:44,250
but they were trying to create
a time differential,

1318
01:01:44,416 --> 01:01:47,333
whether it was in milliseconds
or fractions of a second.

1319
01:01:47,541 --> 01:01:50,708
But it had--
it had to do just with...

1320
01:01:51,750 --> 01:01:53,833
...that force distorting time.

1321
01:01:54,208 --> 01:01:56,958
Now, I mean, we weren't
a 100% sure that...

1322
01:01:57,125 --> 01:01:59,291
that was even gravity
what we were dealing with.

1323
01:01:59,625 --> 01:02:02,166
But anyway, the group that was
working on that was

1324
01:02:02,583 --> 01:02:06,000
attempting to see if that can
distort the flow of time.

1325
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:10,625
The information in the overview
of Project Galileo
was accurate.

1326
01:02:10,916 --> 01:02:13,375
I read the overview and
later witnessed evidence

1327
01:02:13,541 --> 01:02:14,916
which proved it to be accurate.

1328
01:02:15,541 --> 01:02:17,041
So it is possible that

1329
01:02:17,208 --> 01:02:18,750
scientists involved
with other projects,

1330
01:02:19,125 --> 01:02:20,375
could have seen evidence
that these

1331
01:02:20,541 --> 01:02:22,000
other overviews were accurate.

1332
01:02:22,458 --> 01:02:24,458
But I can't make that
assertion.

1333
01:02:24,833 --> 01:02:27,500
To me, these reports were
simply words and pictures
on paper.

1334
01:02:27,916 --> 01:02:29,416
[sharp bang]

1335
01:02:36,208 --> 01:02:38,041
The hangars are all
connected together

1336
01:02:38,208 --> 01:02:40,750
and there are large bay
doors between each one.

1337
01:02:41,166 --> 01:02:44,083
And, uh, there were nine
total that I saw.

1338
01:02:44,250 --> 01:02:46,000
Uh, each one being different.

1339
01:02:47,666 --> 01:02:51,416
I was in the lab with Barry and
Dennis came in and said,

1340
01:02:51,666 --> 01:02:54,333
"We're conducting a test flight,
why don't you guys come out?"

1341
01:02:54,708 --> 01:02:57,500
We left the lab through
the side door,

1342
01:02:57,666 --> 01:03:00,750
which leads directly into
the-- the large hangar.

1343
01:03:00,916 --> 01:03:02,333
And when I opened the door,

1344
01:03:02,625 --> 01:03:06,083
all the doors between the
hangars were open.

1345
01:03:06,250 --> 01:03:10,666
And I looked down and I saw how
big the installation was

1346
01:03:10,833 --> 01:03:13,625
and that there were other craft,

1347
01:03:13,958 --> 01:03:15,583
in those other hangars.

1348
01:03:15,750 --> 01:03:18,500
I couldn't see very far because
they weren't well lit,

1349
01:03:18,708 --> 01:03:21,291
but it did go on
for quite a ways.

1350
01:03:21,541 --> 01:03:25,666
In the hanger adjacent to the
sport model was another craft

1351
01:03:25,958 --> 01:03:27,333
that sometimes I refer to as the

1352
01:03:27,500 --> 01:03:29,708
jello mold or the--
the bundt cake.

1353
01:03:29,875 --> 01:03:32,833
It looks like a bundt cake mold
without the hole in the middle.

1354
01:03:33,083 --> 01:03:36,666
It appeared to be made
of the same material

1355
01:03:36,958 --> 01:03:40,208
as the sport model, same color,
same sheen.

1356
01:03:40,375 --> 01:03:42,291
I couldn't see much
going on with it.

1357
01:03:42,458 --> 01:03:44,125
Again, this was just
a single glance.

1358
01:03:44,291 --> 01:03:47,541
The other craft looked like
a top hat or a straw hat,

1359
01:03:47,708 --> 01:03:50,750
straw carnival hat, uh,
with a large brim on it.

1360
01:03:50,916 --> 01:03:54,166
This one, same color,
same sheen,

1361
01:03:54,333 --> 01:03:56,083
apparently the same material,

1362
01:03:56,291 --> 01:03:59,333
also slightly smaller than
the sport model.

1363
01:03:59,625 --> 01:04:01,375
But this one wasn't laying flat
on the ground.

1364
01:04:01,541 --> 01:04:03,125
It was leaning on the wall.

1365
01:04:03,375 --> 01:04:06,041
And, what was interesting
about this one,

1366
01:04:06,208 --> 01:04:07,666
it had a hole,

1367
01:04:07,833 --> 01:04:10,375
in the side of the brim,
if you wanna call it that,

1368
01:04:10,708 --> 01:04:13,083
as if it was shot from
underneath with a projectile,

1369
01:04:13,250 --> 01:04:15,625
'cause you could see some
of the metal bent outward.

1370
01:04:19,166 --> 01:04:21,791
The craft was already outside
of the hangar.

1371
01:04:21,958 --> 01:04:25,416
There were some researchers and
some other security personnel

1372
01:04:25,583 --> 01:04:28,500
standing at the opening
to the hangar.

1373
01:04:28,916 --> 01:04:30,375
Everybody was looking
at the craft.

1374
01:04:30,541 --> 01:04:33,875
There was, uh, what appeared
to be a VHF radio

1375
01:04:34,041 --> 01:04:36,000
because what caught
my attention was

1376
01:04:36,291 --> 01:04:39,041
they were in communication
with someone in the craft

1377
01:04:39,333 --> 01:04:42,416
and... they were using
a conventional

1378
01:04:42,583 --> 01:04:45,250
VHF radio... to talk to them.

1379
01:04:45,583 --> 01:04:49,541
And I believe it was in the 140
or 150 megahertz bandwidth

1380
01:04:49,708 --> 01:04:52,333
because it said
right on the radio.

1381
01:04:52,500 --> 01:04:54,916
And knowing how
the craft worked,

1382
01:04:55,083 --> 01:04:58,250
it would be impossible
for it to receive

1383
01:04:58,416 --> 01:05:00,958
a radio signal through the
gravitational field.

1384
01:05:01,125 --> 01:05:03,041
I mean, it even--
it bends light around it.

1385
01:05:03,208 --> 01:05:05,958
There's no way a radio wave is
getting inside the craft,

1386
01:05:06,125 --> 01:05:08,375
yet they were talking,
uh, to it.

1387
01:05:08,541 --> 01:05:10,583
So I was really
perplexed by that

1388
01:05:10,750 --> 01:05:12,791
and for a minute just
focused on that

1389
01:05:13,166 --> 01:05:14,916
and looked at the craft and
wondered,

1390
01:05:15,291 --> 01:05:18,041
"You know, obviously there's
something I'm not getting here."

1391
01:05:18,333 --> 01:05:21,416
Dennis instructed me to
go out and I stopped,

1392
01:05:21,666 --> 01:05:24,041
looked at the craft that was
sitting on there and

1393
01:05:24,208 --> 01:05:26,875
began to lift off
the ground silently.

1394
01:05:27,041 --> 01:05:29,458
There was a little hiss from
a corona discharge,

1395
01:05:29,625 --> 01:05:32,250
kind of a bluish purplish
glow at the bottom,

1396
01:05:32,541 --> 01:05:34,666
uh, which dissipated
as it took off.

1397
01:05:34,833 --> 01:05:36,416
Once it was sitting in the air,

1398
01:05:36,583 --> 01:05:38,333
Dennis instructed me
to go further.

1399
01:05:38,625 --> 01:05:39,833
And I went out.

1400
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:41,541
I didn't look up. I was just

1401
01:05:41,708 --> 01:05:44,125
walking forward and then looked
up under the craft

1402
01:05:44,291 --> 01:05:45,666
and I looked back at--

1403
01:05:46,416 --> 01:05:49,250
at Dennis and he motioned me
to come back.

1404
01:05:49,416 --> 01:05:50,791
And I started walking back.

1405
01:05:50,958 --> 01:05:52,333
I saw his hand go up...

1406
01:05:53,416 --> 01:05:56,458
...and he set the indicators for
me to look up and I looked up,

1407
01:05:57,583 --> 01:05:59,416
and the craft wasn't there.

1408
01:06:00,708 --> 01:06:02,250
And I looked over at Dennis

1409
01:06:02,416 --> 01:06:05,416
and he-- he s-- he motioned
for me to go-- go back

1410
01:06:05,583 --> 01:06:08,541
and I-- I looked and
as I moved forward,

1411
01:06:08,791 --> 01:06:10,625
the craft comes into view.

1412
01:06:10,791 --> 01:06:14,875
So you-- you could actually see
the photons bending around

1413
01:06:15,041 --> 01:06:17,750
the gravitational envelope
the-- of the craft.

1414
01:06:17,916 --> 01:06:20,291
You can see the sky
above the craft

1415
01:06:20,541 --> 01:06:24,083
bending and as you walk by,
it comes into view

1416
01:06:24,250 --> 01:06:25,875
and then out of view.
It's really--

1417
01:06:26,041 --> 01:06:28,208
It's-- It really leaves an
impression.

1418
01:06:28,375 --> 01:06:30,000
It's a pretty impressive
thing to see.

1419
01:06:35,708 --> 01:06:37,208
[music fades]

1420
01:06:38,250 --> 01:06:40,500
The hope was ...that...

1421
01:06:41,541 --> 01:06:43,708
...even something small
and insignificant,

1422
01:06:43,875 --> 01:06:45,666
what we would think
is insignificant,

1423
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:47,750
but something small
that we can grasp,

1424
01:06:47,916 --> 01:06:49,916
if we really understood it...

1425
01:06:51,500 --> 01:06:53,750
...as opposed to
a big, complicated--

1426
01:06:53,958 --> 01:06:56,000
you know, like the entire
propulsion system.

1427
01:06:56,166 --> 01:06:58,250
But if you can find
a single piece and...

1428
01:06:58,833 --> 01:07:02,000
just understood exactly
how that worked and how

1429
01:07:02,541 --> 01:07:05,791
their science works, that
that would be the key

1430
01:07:06,333 --> 01:07:08,875
and it would-- the rest would
all fall down like dominoes.

1431
01:07:09,041 --> 01:07:11,125
Like, "Oh, we-- we got it."

1432
01:07:11,291 --> 01:07:13,541
You know, it's like...
[chuckles]

1433
01:07:13,708 --> 01:07:16,416
You know, I have an
understanding of transistor

1434
01:07:16,791 --> 01:07:19,416
and then, "Oh, that's how-- and
a group of these makes an

1435
01:07:19,583 --> 01:07:22,333
integrated circuit and then an
array of these

1436
01:07:22,500 --> 01:07:24,125
and it's in the memory and
computer, I would--

1437
01:07:24,291 --> 01:07:25,958
We got it. It's-- It's done."

1438
01:07:26,125 --> 01:07:29,000
So we were hoping for that
chain reaction to take place.

1439
01:07:29,166 --> 01:07:33,375
Maybe it has, but, um, you know,
when I was there, it was just--

1440
01:07:33,875 --> 01:07:35,875
we wanna focus on some small

1441
01:07:36,291 --> 01:07:38,666
aspects of it,
and see what happens.

1442
01:07:40,750 --> 01:07:42,875
Right, they had a poster
and it looked like a

1443
01:07:43,041 --> 01:07:45,333
commercial poster almost,
like it was lithographed

1444
01:07:45,500 --> 01:07:47,458
and you could buy it at
a K-mart or something,

1445
01:07:47,625 --> 01:07:49,500
but they were all over the
place and it had the--

1446
01:07:50,208 --> 01:07:52,750
the disk that I coined the
term, the sport model

1447
01:07:52,916 --> 01:07:56,500
was lifted off the ground about
three feet at-- at, uh, area S4

1448
01:07:56,666 --> 01:07:58,083
on the dry lake there, and, uh,

1449
01:07:58,250 --> 01:08:00,166
the caption on the bottom said,
"They're here."

1450
01:08:00,708 --> 01:08:03,291
Looked like a commercially
printed poster

1451
01:08:03,458 --> 01:08:06,125
with the sport model
above the desert

1452
01:08:06,291 --> 01:08:08,416
floor that said,
"They're here" on it.

1453
01:08:08,625 --> 01:08:11,500
I-- I can't fathom
why they did that.

1454
01:08:11,666 --> 01:08:13,791
Or for-- Or where they did it,

1455
01:08:14,333 --> 01:08:17,500
